            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-05-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="215" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On February 26, March 8, and March 9, respectively, the Romanian, Bulgarian, and
                    Hungarian Governments were given official notification by the United States
                    Government, in accordance with the treaties of peace with those countries,
                    regarding the pre-war bilateral treaties and other international agreements with
                    Romania, Bulgaria, and Hungary which the United States desired to retain in
                    force or to revive. For the texts of the notes to the Romanian, Bulgarian, and
                    Hungarian Foreign Ministers giving such notification, see the Department of
                    State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 14, 1948, pages 356–357 and March
                    21, 1948, pages 382–384.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
